mmediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/OMNE_Eternal_1002_uraniumBlack_0005-d87f880.png?quality=45&amp;resize=1667%2C1111 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/OMNE_Eternal_1002_uraniumBlack_0005-d87f880.png?quality=45&amp;resize=2222%2C1481 4x\" type=\"image/png\"><img class=\"wp-image-619803 align size-landscape_thumbnail image-handler__image image-handler__image--aspect no-wrap js-lazyload\" data-src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/OMNE_Eternal_1002_uraniumBlack_0005-d87f880.png?quality=90&amp;resize=620%2C413\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"POC Omne Eternal helmet\" title=\"POC Omne Eternal helmet\"></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></picture></div><div class=\"caption-hold\"><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\"><span class=\"caption-copy\"><i class=\"icon-arrow icon-camera-circle\"></i> The three panels on the top with the dot in the middle feature the Powerfoyle material.</span></figcaption><span class=\"im-image-caption\"></span></div>\n<p>Unsurprisingly, the Powerfoyle website doesn’t detail exactly <a href=\"https://www.powerfoyle.com/how-it-works/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">how the technology works</a>, but its key selling point appears to be that it will charge more efficiently from ambient light (even from a bulb) compared to a traditional solar panel, which works best with direct sunlight.</p>\n<p>The generated energy is then used to power an automatically-controlled rear light that is integrated into the back of the helmet.</p>\n<p>This light is powered by the solar cell alone, and its operation is fully passive, so there is no charging cable or power switch. Placing the helmet on your head activates the light. Exactly how this works is not specified.</p>\n<div class=\"image-handler__container image-handler__container--aspect\" style=\"padding-bottom: c